    <abstract>
      <t>A Segment Routing (SR) Policy is a non-empty set of SR Candidate Paths, which share the same &lt;headend, color, endpoint&gt; tuple. SR Policy is modeled in PCEP as an Association of one or more SR Candidate Paths. PCEP extensions are defined to signal additional attributes of an SR Policy. The mechanism is applicable to all SR forwarding planes (MPLS, SRv6, etc.).</t>
